    • Method Detail

      • fetch

        public static UUID fetch(String name)
                  throws IOException,
                         InterruptedException
        Fetches the UUIDs of the given player name from the Mojang API.

        WARNING: this method needs to be called from a dedicated thread, as the requests to Mojang are executed directly in the current thread and, due to the Mojang API rate limit, the thread may be frozen to wait a bit between requests if a lot of UUID are requested.

        You can use a Worker to retrieve UUIDs.

        Parameters:
        name - A player name.
        Returns:
        The player's UUID, or null if it was not found.
        Throws:
        IOException - If an exception occurs while contacting the Mojang API.
        InterruptedException - If the thread is interrupted while sleeping when the system wait because of the Mojang API rate limit.

      • fetch

        public static Map<String,UUID> fetch(List<String> names)
                              throws IOException,
                                     InterruptedException
        Fetches the UUIDs of the given list of player names from the Mojang API.

        WARNING: this method needs to be called from a dedicated thread, as the requests to Mojang are executed directly in the current thread and, due to the Mojang API rate limit, the thread may be frozen to wait a bit between requests if a lot of UUID are requested.

        You can use a Worker to retrieve UUIDs.

        This method may not be able to retrieve UUIDs for some players with old accounts. For them, use fetchRemaining(Collection, Map).

        Parameters:
        names - A list of player names.
        Returns:
        A map linking a player name to his Mojang UUID.
        Throws:
        IOException - If an exception occurs while contacting the Mojang API.
        InterruptedException - If the thread is interrupted while sleeping when the system wait because of the Mojang API rate limit.

                                     int limitByRequest)

        Fetches the UUIDs of the given list of player names from the Mojang API.

        WARNING: this method needs to be called from a dedicated thread, as the requests to Mojang are executed directly in the current thread and, due to the Mojang API rate limit, the thread may be frozen to wait a bit between requests if a lot of UUID are requested.

        You can use a Worker to retrieve UUIDs.

        This method may not be able to retrieve UUIDs for some players with old accounts. For them, use fetchRemaining(Collection, Map).

        Parameters:
        names - A list of player names.
        limitByRequest - The maximal number of UUID to retrieve per request.
        Returns:
        A map linking a player name to his Mojang UUID.
        Throws:
        IOException - If an exception occurs while contacting the Mojang API.
        InterruptedException - If the thread is interrupted while sleeping when the system wait because of the Mojang API rate limit.

      • fetchRemaining

        public static void fetchRemaining(Collection<String> names,
                                  Map<String,UUID> uuids)
                           throws IOException,
                                  InterruptedException
        Terminates the process of UUID fetching against another Mojang API.

        The above methods may not be able to retrieve UUIDs for some players with old accounts. This one will fetch them from another API. But please note that the API used here is way slower than the other one, as only one UUID can be fetched per request, instead of 100 for the other one, and the Mojang servers limit requests rate at one per second. Use it only if needed.

        WARNING: this method needs to be called from a dedicated thread, as the requests to Mojang are executed directly in the current thread and, due to the Mojang API rate limit, the thread may be frozen to wait a bit between requests if more than one UUID is requested.

        Parameters:
        names - The complete list of names to retrieve.
        uuids - The UUIDs already retrieved by the fetch(List) or fetch(List, int) methods. This map will be completed with the missing UUIDs.
        Throws:
        IOException - If an exception occurs while contacting the Mojang API.
        InterruptedException - If the thread is interrupted while sleeping when the system wait because of the Mojang API rate limit.
